A potential fix for Border#shrink might be:
    public Rectanglei shrink(Rectanglei region) {
        final Rectanglei shrunk = RectUtility.createFromMinAndSize(region.minX + getLeft(), region.minY + getTop(),
                region.lengthX() - getTotalWidth(), region.lengthY() - getTotalHeight());
        return shrunk.isValid() ? shrunk : new Rectanglei();
    }
This mimics the behavior of Rect2i::createFromMinAndSize
    public static Rect2i createFromMinAndSize(int x, int y, int width, int height) {
        if (width <= 0 || height <= 0) {
            return EMPTY;
        }
        return new Rect2i(x, y, width, height);
    }
